namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.

So for example, in this product master templates, we have this particular template for mouse pad.
This is a template for a mouse pad.
But for example, you want this template the same template in business card.
So in that case you will need to create a new version.
So to create a new version, you just go to the particular template, click on action button, click on Create new version.
Here first of all select the user type, then select the product for which you want to create the new version.
So we want to create a new version for the standard business card.
So here we'll select the standard business card sized 2 by 3.5.

So you will need to resize the template.
So for that activate this resize template button.

After that just simply select the sort order and click on 7 continue.

So now you can see a new version of a template is created for the business card 2 by 3.5.
So this is how you can create a new version of a template.
Now how to duplicate a template or how to duplicate the templates.
So for that go to admin panel templates and then click on duplicate templates.
Here you have three option Add duplicate templates, remove duplicate templates and duplicate templates with resize.

So if you want to add duplicate templates to add the duplicate templates when you select the products the both the products should be of the same size the source product and for the product for which you want to duplicate the template both the products should be of the same size.
Then and only then you will be able to duplicate the templates.
So add duplicate templates select the user type.
After selecting the user type, select the product from which you want to duplicate the template.
To add the duplicate templates, both the products should be of the same size.
The source product from which you want to duplicate the template and the product for which you want to duplicate the template.

Now from here, you can select which templates you want to duplicate.

So once again, let's go to the storefront and check the business card 16 point whether the templates are duplicated or not.

From here you can select which duplicate templates you want to remove like say PDF block template, Master template or product templates and then just click on save button.
Now click on save button.

So as we have removed the duplicate templates, let's check it on storefront.
So you can see business card 16 point.
Right now these are the available templates.
Now when we refresh, you can see the templates are removed, The duplicate templates are removed.
Then comes the duplicate templates with resize.
I will highly recommend that don't use these option.
If you want to duplicate template with resize then use the option of create new version which I have shown you before.
Because in this option it is written that duplicate templates with resize.
But here the templates are not duplicated or copied.
They are resized and moved from one product to the other product and once they are moved from one product to the other product, they cannot be reverted back to the original product.
So that is why I will not recommend to use these option.
But I will show you how you can use it.
You can select the template type from here as a product templates or mask templates.
Then you can select the product from here for the particular template.

Just go to the particular template, click on Action button, Create new Version and use the option of Resize template from here.
So this is how you can create new version and duplicate templates.
Thank you for watching this video.
